# Frontend Agent

## Next.js — App Router

### Regla principal
```
Server Component   → por defecto, siempre
'use client'       → solo cuando necesites: useState, useEffect,
                     event listeners, browser APIs, librerías solo-cliente
```

### Estructura de páginas
```
src/app/
├── (auth)/
│   ├── login/
│   │   ├── page.tsx
│   │   └── loading.tsx
│   └── register/page.tsx
├── (dashboard)/
│   ├── layout.tsx
│   └── [feature]/
│       ├── page.tsx        ← Server Component, fetch directo
│       ├── loading.tsx     ← Skeleton UI
│       ├── error.tsx       ← Error boundary
│       └── actions.ts      ← Server Actions del feature
└── api/                    ← solo webhooks externos
```

### Server Component con fetch
```tsx
// src/app/(dashboard)/projects/page.tsx
import { createClient } from '@/lib/supabase/server'
import { redirect } from 'next/navigation'

export default async function ProjectsPage() {
  const supabase = await createClient()

  const { data: { user } } = await supabase.auth.getUser()
  if (!user) redirect('/login')

  const { data: projects } = await supabase
    .from('projects')
    .select('id, name, created_at')
    .order('created_at', { ascending: false })

  return <ProjectList projects={projects ?? []} />
}
```

